## 📖 THE STORY

Investigative journalist **Priya Singh** was found dead in her apartment. Authorities ruled it a natural cardiac arrest and closed the case within 48 hours.

Intelligence sources disagree.

Priya was working on a story that could bring down a powerful corporation. Her data was wiped. Her story was buried. Her killers are still free.

**Your team's mission:** Infiltrate the company network, recover deleted evidence, and piece together the final 11 minutes of her life.

---

## 👥 YOUR TEAM (READ THIS FIRST!)

You and your partner are NOT playing the same game. You each have **different abilities** and **see different things** on your screens. This is intentional.

> ⚠️ **The most important rule of this game is: TALK TO EACH OTHER.**
> You cannot win alone. You will need to describe what you see, ask questions, and coordinate every step.

### 🟢 FIELD AGENT (1st Year Student)
You are the one on the ground — the infiltrator. You have the technical skills to run raw code and navigate the physical space.

**What you can do:**
- ✅ Execute **Python** code in the terminal
- ✅ Move your character around the **2D map** (WASD / Arrow Keys)
- ✅ Physically pick up items and interact with objects
- ❌ Cannot use the HTML/CSS editor (your partner handles this)
- ❌ Cannot see security bots on the map (your partner must warn you!)

---

### 🔵 INTEL OFFICER (2nd Year Student)
You are the overwatch — the analyst. You have high-level access to structural systems and databases.

**What you can do:**
- ✅ Edit **HTML** and **CSS** code in the editor
- ✅ Run **SQL queries** on the case database (Round 1)
- ✅ See **Sec-Bots** and their patrol routes on the map — warn your Field Agent!
- ✅ Solve hacking minigames that appear when terminals are accessed
- ❌ Cannot move the player character on the map
- ❌ Cannot execute Python code

